<h1><img src="/pub/Graphics/Icons/eff3d_trans_icon.gif" ALT="">
<a name="top">EFF &quot;Net-Tools - Archival/Compression - Windows&quot; Archive</a></h1>

<H5>http://www.eff.org/pub/Net_info/Tools/Win/Archive_comp/
</H5>



<TABLE BORDER=4 CELLPADDING=4 CELLSPACING=4>
<TR ALIGN=CENTER>
<TD><A HREF="#files">Files</A></TD><H1></H1>
<TD><A HREF="#dirs">Subdirectories</A></TD><H1></H1>
<TD><A HREF="#onsite">On-Site Links</A></TD><H1></H1>
<TD><A HREF="#offsite">Off-Site Links</A></TD>
</TR></TABLE>


<P></CENTER><BR><HR>
<BR><h2><A NAME="files">
<IMG SRC="/pub/Graphics/Icons/doc1_icon.gif" ALT=""></A>
Files in this Archive</h2>

<DL>
<DT><a href="wincode.zip"><B>wincode.zip</B></a>
<DD>Windows utils to encode/decode MIME/Base64, uuencode and 
    xxencode files (like BinHex, these encoding schemes turn binaries into 
    7-bit ASCII files that can be emailed or posted to Usenet.)
</DL>

