<P></CENTER><BR><HR>
<BR><h2><A NAME="files"></a>
<IMG SRC="/pub/Graphics/Icons/doc1_icon.gif" ALT=""></A>
Files in this Archive</h2>

<DL>
<DT><a href="cpsr_clipper.statement"><B>cpsr_clipper.statement</B></a>
<DD>1993 article of CPSR's call for public debate
    on the encryption initiative
<DT><a href="cpsr_crypto.article"><B>cpsr_crypto.article</B></a>
<DD>David Sobel's 1992 discussion of the controversy
    over NIST standardization of DSS and related
    intellectual property issues.
<DT><a href="cpsr_v_govt_secrecy.statement"><B>cpsr_v_govt_secrecy.statement</B></a>
<DD>cpsr's 1993 attack on Reagan's "secrecy 
    directive" allowing the NSA to classify information concerning
    cryptology
<DT><a href="cpsr_v_nsa.note"><B>cpsr_v_nsa.note</B></a>
<DD>David Sobel's article discussing the NSA's attempts to
    stall a CPSR lawsuit against it to make the "Clipper" proposal public.
<DT><a href="dss_cpsr.brief"><B>dss_cpsr.brief</B></a>
<DD>1992 CPSR v NIST brief in which CPSR demanded disclosure 
    of documents involving DSS
<DT><a href="epic_clipper_foia_1095.announce"><B>epic_clipper_foia_1095.announce</B></a>
<DD>EPIC press relase regaring renewed
    efforts to obtain information from NSA about Clipper and Administration
    crypto policy. Refers to a brief EPIC submitted in support of CPSR's
    FOIA lawsuit against NSA (see epic_clipper_foia_1095.brief below).
<DT><a href="epic_clipper_foia_1095.brief"><B>epic_clipper_foia_1095.brief</B></a>
<DD>EPIC amicus brief filed in support of CPSR's
    lawsuit against the NSA. Argues forcefully that NSA is prevaricating,
    that Clipper was classified for law enforcement convenience and political
    value, rather than "national security".
<DT><a href="nsc_reply_to_cpsr.letter"><B>nsc_reply_to_cpsr.letter</B></a>
<DD>1992 letter from NSC to Marc Rotenberg
    containing unclassified segments of the national policy for the
    security of national security telecommunications and information systems
</DL>

