<P></CENTER><BR><HR>
<BR><h2><A NAME="files">
<IMG SRC="/pub/Graphics/Icons/doc1_icon.gif" ALT=""></A>
Files in this Archive</h2>

<DL>
<DT><a href="binhex.zip"><B>binhex.zip</B></a>
<DD>A DOS encoder/decoder for BinHex (.hqx) files. BinHex is 
    like uu- and xxencoding, and MIME: a way to turn binaries temporarily into
    text files so that they can be emailed or posted to Usenet. BinHex is
    mostly used by Mac users.
<DT><a href="gzip124.zip"><B>gzip124.zip</B></a>
<DD>DOS util to create or decompress Unix gnu-zip (.gz) and
    compress (.Z) files.
<DT><a href="pkz204g.exe"><B>pkz204g.exe</B></a>
<DD>PKUnZip, the tool needed to extract .zip/.ZIP files on a
    DOS PC. Absolutely essential tool for any DOS user with a
    modem. This is a self-extracting archive. Just type
    PKZ204G when you get it home. Also includes PKZip, the util
    used to create ZIP files.
<DT><a href="unstuff1.zip"><B>unstuff1.zip</B></a>
<DD>DOS program to extract files from Mac StuffIt (.sit, .sea)
    compressed archives. This file is ZIP archived.
</DL>

