<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>What is a hacker</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR = "FFFFFF" TEXT = "000000">
<BLOCKQUOTE>

<H2><CENTER>What is a Hacker</CENTER></H2>

Hacking is a lot of things to alot of people, there is no good way to
explain it.  However, it is certainly not limited to computer nerds
breaking into computer systems.  Hacking might be finding a better way to
make a program work...or it might be playing games, it might be political
with an anarchist agenda, it might be a process or product, thing or
theology, a way of life or just something you do once...it might be
solving a riddle, getting even, causing panic, creating knowledge. 
Hackers are men, women, children, and if their email address are correct
lobsters from Mars.  And hacking is certainly not limited to
computers...are hip hop artists musical hackers?  Was McLuhan a social
hacker? 

<P>

I suggest you do some reading at
<A HREF = "http://www.eff.org/pub/Net_culture/Hackers/">EFF's Hacker 
Archive</A> 

</BLOCKQUOTE>
</BODY></HTML>
</DOC>
