<HEAD><TITLE>Index of /pub/Net_info/Guidebooks/Hytelnet/Mac</TITLE></HEAD><BODY>
<H1>Index of /pub/Net_info/Guidebooks/Hytelnet/Mac</H1>
<PRE><IMG SRC="/icons/blank.xbm" ALT="     "> Name                   Last modified     Size  Description
<HR>
<IMG SRC="/icons/back.xbm" ALT="[DIR]"> <A HREF="/pub/Net_info/Guidebooks/Hytelnet/">Parent Directory</A>       17-Oct-96 12:00      -  
<IMG SRC="/icons/unknown.xbm" ALT="[   ]"> <A HREF="hytelnet6.6.1.supplement.sit.hqx">hytelnet6.6.1.supplem..</A>25-Jan-94 14:39    76k  
<IMG SRC="/icons/unknown.xbm" ALT="[   ]"> <A HREF="hytelnet6.6.sea.hqx">hytelnet6.6.sea.hqx</A>    25-Jan-94 08:59   926k  
</PRE><HR>
<PRE>
[Note! See README.new - contains info on new update.]

Hytelnet for the Macintosh version 6.6

Hytelnet is a user friendly front end to a large database of
internet accessable library and information servces.

This file is a binhexed self extracting archive that contains:
	- Hytelnet Reader
	- Information document in old MacWrite format
	- Hytelnet Data files.

The file may be un-binhexed using one of the following programs:
	- mcvert available on many Unix hosts
	- Any of the stuffit line of programs (stuffit expander,
	  stuffit deluxe, stuffit lite)
	- Compator pro
	- binhex 4.0
	- A variety of other archiving packages

The Macintosh version will:
	- automatically open NCSA telnet 
	  and connect to remote sites.
	- update the Hytelnet database using files from the
	  HYTEL-l list serv or usenet group.
	- Read PC files over a network.  It will also update
	  a networked PC database from the Hytel-l list serv files.
	
Essential Files:
	- HyperCard 2.1 (or HyperCard Player)
	- System 7.0 is prefered
	- Hytelnet data directory and files.
	
The author of the Macintosh front end can be contacted through
electronic mail at: &lt;burchil@cc.umanitoba.ca&gt;

Thanks for supporting Hytelnet.

</PRE>
</BODY>
