<h1><img src="/pub/Graphics/Icons/eff3d_white_icon.gif" ALT="">
<a name="top">EFF &quot;Legal Cases - Crypto - Bernstein v. US Dept. of State&quot; Archive</a></h1>

<H5>http://www.eff.org/pub/Privacy/ITAR_export/Bernstein_case/
</H5>



<h6>Last Updated Mon Dec 30 21:58:21 PDT 1996</h6><br>
<br>
   An EFF-sponsored lawsuit by Professor Daniel Bernstein
   to determine whether the Professor has the right to teach
   about cryptography, and collaborate with his peers around the
   world. A major point is whether he can publish source code that foreigners
   might be able to access, or speak it directly to individual who might
   be foreign. The case rests on established First Amendment law
   and relies on the fact that computer source code is human-to-human
   communication protected by the First Amendment (in addition to anything
   else it might be useful for.)
<p>
<TABLE BORDER=4 CELLPADDING=4 CELLSPACING=4>
<TR ALIGN=CENTER>
<TD><A HREF="#files">Files</A></TD><h6></h6>
<TD><A HREF="#dirs">Subdirectories</A></TD><h6></h6>
<TD><A HREF="#onsite">On-Site Links</A></TD><h6></h6>
<TD><A HREF="#offsite">Off-Site Links</A></TD>
</TR></TABLE>


<P></CENTER><BR><HR>
<BR><h2><A NAME="files">
<IMG SRC="/pub/Graphics/Icons/doc1_icon.gif" WIDTH=40 HEIGHT=40 ALT=""></A>
Files in this Archive</h2>

<DL>
<DT><a href="961230.pressrel"><B>961230.pressrel</B></a>
<DD>EFF press release about letter from Bernstein's
    counsel asking the government to stipulate to not enforcing the
    Commerce Department regulations until they have been reviewed by the
    court for Constitutionality.
<DT><a href="961218_pressrel.html"><B>961218_pressrel.html</B></a>
<DD>EFF announcement of Judge Patel's decision
    striking down parts of the export control laws as unconstitutional.
    (HTML version)
<DT><a href="961218.pressrel"><B>961218.pressrel</B></a>
<DD>EFF announcement of Judge Patel's decision
    striking down parts of the export control laws as unconstitutional.
    (text version)
<DT><a href="960918.pressrel"><B>960918.pressrel</B></a>
<DD>EFF press release announcing the September 20th hearing.
<DT><a href="960726.pressrel"><B>960726.pressrel</B></a>
<DD>EFF press release on our partial summary judgement filing.
<DT><a href="960417.pressrel"><B>960417.pressrel</B></a>
<DD>EFF press release on Judge Patel's decision to 
    deny the government's request to dismiss Bernstein case, and her 
    acknowledgement that source code is protected speech.
<DT><a href="951020.alert"><B>951020.alert</B></a>
<DD>announcement of first court date for oral 
    arguments in the Bernstein case (Oct. 20, 1995).
<DT><a href="950221.pressrel"><B>950221.pressrel</B></a>
<DD>EFF's press release on the filing of this case.
<DT><a href="9502xx_60minutes.letter"><B>9502xx_60minutes.letter</B></a>
<DD>Letter from EFF to producers of _60_Minutes_
    news program, criticizing
    a _60_Minutes_ profile of Internet security that failed to
    mention encryption. Letter points out crypto's essential role in data
    security, and introduces the EFF/Bernstein v. Dept. of State/NSA 
    lawsuit.
<DT><a href="eff_bernstein_950221.complaint"><B>eff_bernstein_950221.complaint</B></a>
<DD>The complaint (charges) filed by EFF and 
    Dan Bernstein against the State Dept., 
    et al., for violation of First Amendment
    free speech rights via ITAR crypto export
    restrictions.
<DT><a href="930326_ray.transcript"><B>930326_ray.transcript</B></a>
<DD>A revealing and frustrating transcript of a
    discussion between Dan Bernstein and Charles Ray (of the
    Office of Defense Trade Controls, which enforced the export control
    laws at that time).
<DT><a href="oconnor.article"><B>oconnor.article</B></a>
<DD>&quot;Mathematician challenges U.S. lid on encryption software&quot;
    article by Rory J. O'Connor on the Bernstein case, from 
    _San_Jose_Mercury_News_.
</DL>

