<P></CENTER><BR><HR>
<BR><h2><A NAME="files">
<IMG SRC="/pub/Graphics/Icons/doc1_icon.gif" ALT=""></A>
Files in this Archive</h2>

These are the letters written by Dan Bernstein and by the Office of Defense Trad Controls, regarding Bernstein's Snuffle encryption program, which the ODTC has obstinately regarded as a "defense article," with all the limitations upon export, etc., that go with that designation.  Bernstein's case is now in court, and is considered a prime testing ground for the legality of current restrictions upon encryption algorithms.

<DL>
<DT><a href="920630_cj.letter"><B>920630_cj.letter</B></a>
<DD>No Description
<DT><a href="920820_cjrej.letter"><B>920820_cjrej.letter</B></a>
<DD>No Description
<DT><a href="930319_pd.letter"><B>930319_pd.letter</B></a>
<DD>No Description
<DT><a href="930402_loop.letter"><B>930402_loop.letter</B></a>
<DD>No Description
<DT><a href="930520_dellums.letter"><B>930520_dellums.letter</B></a>
<DD>No Description
<DT><a href="930527_bryant.letter"><B>930527_bryant.letter</B></a>
<DD>No Description
<DT><a href="930630_rob.letter"><B>930630_rob.letter</B></a>
<DD>No Description
<DT><a href="930709_rob.letter"><B>930709_rob.letter</B></a>
<DD>No Description
<DT><a href="930714_dellums.letter"><B>930714_dellums.letter</B></a>
<DD>No Description
<DT><a href="README"><B>README</B></a>
<DD>Dan Bernstein offers the best introduction to these letters himself.
</DL>

