<HEAD>
<TITLE>Eric Tachibana's Resume - Applications Development</TITLE>
</HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR = "FFFFFF" TEXT = "000000">
<H2><CENTER>Eric Tachibana's Resume - Applications Development</H2></CENTER>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
At the end of 1996, the National Center for Human Genome Research (NCHGR), 
decided to drop the use of Lotus Notes as their groupware standard in 
favor of a web-based intranet.  As webmaster, I has the pleasure of being 
asked to replicate the functionality of Lotus Notes on the web to the 
best of my ability.  

<P>

In a matter of months I was able to develop CGI-based versions of a
groupware calendar, a bulletin/discussion board, a sitewide keyword search
engine, and helped in the development of a real-time chat program.  These
applications have been heavily used for a multitude of intranet
applications. 

<P>

As with all of my work, script text and working examples are available 
as public domain freeware at 
<A HREF = "http://www.eff.org/~erict/Scritps">Selena Sol's Public Domain 
Scripts Archive</A>

</BLOCKQUOTE></BODY></HTML>
</DOC>
