<BR><h2><A NAME="files"></a>
<IMG SRC="/pub/Graphics/Icons/doc1_icon.gif" ALT=""></A>
Files in this Archive</h2>

<DL>
<DT><a href="07-18-93_opposing_dismissal.statement"><B>07-18-93_opposing_dismissal.statement</B></a>
<DD>Lee Tien's July 1993
    NSA suit update memo concerning the NSA's illegally slow response time for
    FOIA requests.
<DT><a href="09-09-93.letter"><B>09-09-93.letter</B></a>
<DD>Robert Prestel's (NSA) response to Lee 
    Tien's request through FOIA for portions of "Military Cryptoanalysis" by 
    William Friedman and "Military Cryptanalytics" by Lambros 
    Callimahos. Mr. Tien claims he is being denied access to these 
    documents. Prestel advices patience. 
<DT><a href="10-02-93.letter"><B>10-02-93.letter</B></a>
<DD>Michael Smith's (NSA) October 1992 
    letter to Lee Tien upholding the "classified" rating of the documents 
    sought after by Tien. It also deals with the process of processing 
    requests.
<DT><a href="continuation.agreement"><B>continuation.agreement</B></a>
<DD>stipulation and agreement between 
    plaintiff (Lee tien/John Gilmore) and defendant (NSA) to continue the 
    December 21, 1992 hearing and status conference regarding the FOIA suit.
<DT><a href="itar_1st_amend.biblio"><B>itar_1st_amend.biblio</B></a>
<DD>June 1993 letter from Lee Tien on 
    to Clyde Bryant DoS) explaining why ITAR (International Traffic in
    Arms Regulations), which includes information about cryptography, 
    violates first amendment rights. 
<DT><a href="michael_smith.declaration"><B>michael_smith.declaration</B></a>
<DD>Michael Smith's (NSA) November 
    1992 declaration to the US District Court for N. Calif
    regarding the NSA arguments for secrecy regarding the documents John 
    Gilmore requested through FOIA (Freedom of Information Act).
<DT><a href="nsa_defense.answer"><B>nsa_defense.answer</B></a>
<DD>NSA's answers to questions posed 
    by John Gilmore and Lee Tien regarding file complaint. NSA claims the 
    records requested under FOIA are exempt.
<DT><a href="nsa_status.certificate"><B>nsa_status.certificate</B></a>
<DD>Sept 1992 summary of the status of 
    the FOIA lawsuit. This stuff is really tedious... 
<DT><a href="staying_order.memo"><B>staying_order.memo</B></a>
<DD>December 1992 arguments in support of 
    defendant's motion for protective order staying discovery; preliminary 
    statement.
<DT><a href="summary_judgement.memo"><B>summary_judgement.memo</B></a>
<DD>NSA's arguments for why the court 
    should rule in favor of the NSA, dated December 1992. 
<DT><a href="summary_judgement.notice"><B>summary_judgement.notice</B></a>
<DD>December 1992 notice of motion 
    and motion for summary judgement.
<DT><a href="summary_judgement.order"><B>summary_judgement.order</B></a>
<DD>court ordered grant of 
    defendant's (NSA) summary judgement.
<DT><a href="undisputed_facts.statement"><B>undisputed_facts.statement</B></a>
<DD>defendant's statement of 
    material facts not indispute ("In support of defendant's Motion for 
    Summary Judgment, and in accordance with Local Rule 220(7), defendant 
    states the following material facts as to which there is no genuine 
    dispute...')
</DL>

