<BR><h2><A NAME="files">
<IMG SRC="/pub/Graphics/Icons/doc1_icon.gif" ALT=""></A>
Files in this Archive</h2>

<DL>
<DT><a href="ca_cde_gopher.announce"><B>ca_cde_gopher.announce</B></a>
<DD>The California Department of Education (CDE)
    proudly announces the addition of its new gopher server to the Internet
<DT><a href="ca_gov_info.faq"><B>ca_gov_info.faq</B></a>
<DD>Chris May's June 1994 announcement &quot;California
    Electronic Government Information Archived&quot; which includes
    information on California government sources of electronic
    information that are currently available to the public, either by
    means of the Internet or by direct dial to a bulletin board system
<DT><a href="ca_legis_online.article"><B>ca_legis_online.article</B></a>
<DD>Information abou the California Senate on-line 
    services
<DT><a href="ca_legis_online.faq"><B>ca_legis_online.faq</B></a>
<DD>Malcom Sharp's Jan 1994 announcement that
    Information regarding matters pending before the California Legislature
    that has been available to the public in printed form since 1849 is now
    available over Internet. He also provides information that will assist
    the general public in obtaining legislative information for the State
    of California from the public access computer
<DT><a href="mail2fax_sacto.announce"><B>mail2fax_sacto.announce</B></a>
<DD>Gerald Klass' Feb 1994 announcement that he has
    created an e-mail to FAX gateway in Sacramento which may be used to 
    &quot;e-mail&quot; State legislators.
<DT><a href="sf_info_access.article"><B>sf_info_access.article</B></a>
<DD>Feb 1994 Bay Gaurdian article announcing that San
    Francisco has expanded its public access breaking the city's Sunshine
    Law which overcharged citizens for copies of computerized public records
</DL>

