<h1><img src="/pub/Graphics/Icons/eff3d_white_icon.gif" ALT="">
<a name="top">EFF &quot;Net Tools - Privacy &amp; Security - Steganography&quot; Archive</a></h1>

<H5>http://www.eff.org/pub/Net_info/Tools/Crypto/Steganography/
</H5>



<TABLE BORDER=4 CELLPADDING=4 CELLSPACING=4>
<TR ALIGN=CENTER>
<TD><A HREF="#files">Files</A></TD><H1></H1>
<TD><A HREF="#dirs">Subdirectories</A></TD><H1></H1>
<TD><A HREF="#onsite">On-Site Links</A></TD><H1></H1>
<TD><A HREF="#offsite">Off-Site Links</A></TD>
</TR></TABLE>


<P></CENTER><BR><HR>
<BR><h2><A NAME="files">
<IMG SRC="/pub/Graphics/Icons/doc1_icon.gif" ALT=""></A>
Files in this Archive</h2>

<DL>
<DT><a href="stealth.tar.gz"><B>stealth.tar.gz</B></a>
<DD>Stealth 1.0 is a simple filter for PGP which strips off all
    identifying header information to leave only the encrypted data in a
    format suitable for steganographic use. That is, the data can be hidden in
    images, audio files, text files, CAD files, and/or any other file type that
    may contain random data, then sent to another person who can retrieve the
    data from the file, attach headers, and PGP decrypt it. This does NOT
    contain crypto code or any other export-restricted material, and is only a
    filter. This is the Unix (source) version, as a gzip-compressed tar 
    archive.
<DT><a href="stealth.zip"><B>stealth.zip</B></a>
<DD>as stealth.tar.gz above; this is the DOS (source, no exectuables
    included) version, ZIP-compressed.
<DT><a href="stegware.list"><B>stegware.list</B></a>
<DD>Brief descriptions of steganographic programs.
</DL>

