<P></CENTER><BR><HR>
<BR><h2><A NAME="files">
<IMG SRC="/pub/Graphics/Icons/doc1_icon.gif" WIDTH=40 HEIGHT=40 ALT=""></A>
Files in this Archive</h2>

<DL>
<DT><a href="README"><B>README</B></a>
<DD>the EFF's Guide to the Internet Frequently Asked Questions (and 
    Answers) list.
<DT><a href="README.VMS"><B>README.VMS</B></a>
<DD>info on the Guide for users of the VMS operating system.
<DT><a href="README.making_new_versions"><B>README.making_new_versions</B></a>
<DD>Notes on making new formats and translations
    of the EFF Guide to the Internet.
<DT><a href="README.netgddos"><B>README.netgddos</B></a>
<DD>Authorship notes for netgddos.zip
<DT><a href="eegtti-2.3.tar.gz"><B>eegtti-2.3.tar.gz</B></a>
<DD>Texinfo sources for all of versions of the Guide below
    (principally for Unix systems with TeX, and for those wishing to 
    produce specialized Info, DVI, PS, etc. versions, e.g. legal size, 
    custom typeset versions, etc.)
<DT><a href="eegtti-2.3-us.dvi.gz"><B>eegtti-2.3-us.dvi.gz</B></a>
<DD>Device Independent (DVI), US letter size, version of
    the Guide.
<DT><a href="eegtti-2.3-us.ps.gz"><B>eegtti-2.3-us.ps.gz</B></a>
<DD>PostScript (PS), US letter size, version of the Guide.
<DT><a href="eegtti-2.3.amiga.lha"><B>eegtti-2.3.amiga.lha</B></a>
<DD>AmigaGuide version of the Guide, for the Commodore
    Amiga
<DT><a href="eegtti-2.3.dvi.gz"><B>eegtti-2.3.dvi.gz</B></a>
<DD>Device Independent (DVI), European A4 size, vers. of
    the Guide
<DT><a href="eegtti-2.3.html.tar.gz"><B>eegtti-2.3.html.tar.gz</B></a>
<DD>HTML (World Wide Web) hypertext version of the
    Guide, for placing for public view on WWW servers, and for personal 
    viewing with HTML browsers like Netscape, Mosaic, Cello, MacWeb and Lynx.
<DT><a href="eegtti-2.3.info.gz"><B>eegtti-2.3.info.gz</B></a>
<DD>Gnu Info version of the Guide (for Unix).
<DT><a href="eegtti-2.3.ps.gz"><B>eegtti-2.3.ps.gz</B></a>
<DD>PostScript (PS), Eur. A4 size, version of the Guide.
<DT><a href="eegtti-2.3.txt.gz"><B>eegtti-2.3.txt.gz</B></a>
<DD>ASCII text version derived from the Texinfo sources
    (differs from &quot;official&quot; text version in that it includes some extra 
    intro material and appendices.)
<DT><a href="egtti-3.1_view.cpt.hqx"><B>egtti-3.1_view.cpt.hqx</B></a>
<DD>EasyView view file for egtti-3_1.etx (used by the
    Mac Setext viewer, EasyView)
<DT><a href="egtti-3_1.etx"><B>egtti-3_1.etx</B></a>
<DD>Setext version. Setext is a special markup format to
    make ASCII text more readable. You can view this as an
    ASCII text file, or in a special Setext brower, which will
    give you some hypertext capabilities. See ftp.eff.org, 
    /pub/Net_info/Tools/HTML_Setext_Acrobat/ for Setext browsers.
<DT><a href="netg-win.zip"><B>netg-win.zip</B></a>
<DD>Windows Help (.HLP) searchable hypertext version of the Guide.
    by Cesare Feroldi de Rosa. Currently at ver. 3.11 of the Guide.
<DT><a href="netgd-dw.zip"><B>netgd-dw.zip</B></a>
<DD>A colorful, hypertext version of the Guide that you can 
    read on PCs running DOS and/or MS-Windows 3.1. You can consult this 
    version of the Guide whether you're on-line or off-line. Currently at
    v. 3.11 of the Guide (Aug. 1995). For comments and questions, contact
    levner@panix.com.
<DT><a href="netgddos.zip"><B>netgddos.zip</B></a>
<DD>a DOS hypertext version of the Guide, with viewer (SAGE.EXE).
    (currently at version 3.14 of the Guide or newer.)
<DT><a href="netgdos2.zip"><B>netgdos2.zip</B></a>
<DD>another DOS version of the guide, in Rouge Valley Software's
    browser format. Not a true hypertext; more linear, like a book.
<DT><a href="netghypr.wp6"><B>netghypr.wp6</B></a>
<DD>A WordPerfect version of the guide, with hypertextual links
    produced by Michael Frumer (mfrumer@astro.ocis.temple.edu) and his 
    original WP scripts. This version should work fine in the following 
    versions of WP: Windows 6.x, DOS 6.x, most Unix 6.x, Mac 3.5 (when 
    available.) NOTE: This is NOT a text file. Transfer in *binary* mode.
<DT><a href="netguide.changes.gz"><B>netguide.changes.gz</B></a>
<DD>a copy of the full current version of the guide, with
    changes from previous version indicated by &quot;|&quot; before changed lines 
    (this version created with Gnu wdiff). This is a gzip-compressed 
    ASCII file.
<DT><a href="netguide.wd2"><B>netguide.wd2</B></a>
<DD>MS Word for Windows 2.0 version of EFF's Guide to the 
    Internet. Should be readable by MacWord and many other word 
    processors that can import WinWord documents. Currently at version 
    3.18 of the guide. Proportioned for printing on European A4 paper.
    Prepared by Hugues Mercusot &lt;mercusot_h@decus.fr&gt;.
</DL>

<br><hr><br>
<H2><A NAME="dirs">
<IMG SRC="/pub/Graphics/Icons/filefolder_icon.gif" WIDTH=40 HEIGHT=40
ALT=""></A> Subdirectories in This Archive</H2>

<DL>
<DT><A HREF=".."><B>Up to the Parent Directory</B><P></a>
<DT><a href="French/"><B>French/</B></A>
<DD>(a.k.a. Francais/) directory containing French versions of the
    EFF Net Guide. [Guide EFF de L`Internet, edition Francais.]
<DT><a href="Hungarian/"><B>Hungarian/</B></A>
<DD>(a.k.a. Magyar/) directory containing Hungarian versions
    of the EFF Net Guide and Updates. [A Kalauz Magyar valtozatai.]
<DT><a href="Italian/"><B>Italian/</B></A>
<DD>directory containing Italian versions of the EFF Net Guide 
    and updates [Guida a Internet della EFF &amp; Aggiornamentos.]
<DT><a href="Japanese/"><B>Japanese/</B></A>
<DD>(a.k.a. Kanji_SGIS/) directory containing Japanese Kanji versions
    of the EFF Net Guide (in SJIS text and MSWord 6.0).
<DT><a href="Old/"><B>Old/</B></A>
<DD>Directory containing obsolete versions that are otherwise unique.
    Old versions of material available in a newer version are not kept,
    only old versions in formats that are no longer produced (e.g. because
    the volunteer producing them has stopped doing so) are archived here,
    and will remain only until they are replaced by updated versions by
    new volunteers.
    Ex: Mac HyperCard format.
<DT><a href="Polish/"><B>Polish/</B></A>
<DD>Directory containing Polish versions of the Guide.
<DT><a href="Split/"><B>Split/</B></A>
<DD>Directory containing the ASCII text version split into small pieces.
    This is used for mailing the guide from the netguide@eff.org infobot
    (split so that it is not truncated by misbehaving mail gateways.) 
    It is made publicly accessible for download as well, just in case
    someone finds a use for it in this condition. 
</DL>

