<DD>short article by Bruce Sterling about
    the collection of decrepit and obsolete computer equipment and supplies.
<DT><a href="dead_media.notes"><B>dead_media.notes</B></a>
<DD>Full notes from the Dead Media Project. Includes 
    introduction to the DMP, the definitive dead media list, and full text of 
    all documentary notes DMP has collected about each dead medium.
    Warning: Large file (over 500K).
<DT><a href="dmp_sterling.proposal"><B>dmp_sterling.proposal</B></a>
<DD>initial proposal for and introduction to the Dead 
    Media Project, by Bruce Sterling.
<DT><a href="media_life_death_sterling.speech"><B>media_life_death_sterling.speech</B></a>
<DD>&quot;The Life and Death of Media&quot;,
    Speech at Sixth International Symposium on Electronic Art, ISEA '95
    Montreal, Canada, Sept. 19 1995, by Bruce Sterling. Genesis of the Dead
    Media Project.
</DL>

