<P></CENTER><BR><HR>
<BR><h2><A NAME="files">
<IMG SRC="/pub/Graphics/Icons/doc1_icon.gif" ALT=""></A>
Files in this Archive</h2>

<DL>
<DT><a href="crlp_020796.complaint"><B>crlp_020796.complaint</B></a>
<DD>the full text of the Center for Reproductive 
    Law &amp; Policy, Planned Parenthood (NYC), Intl. Women's Human Rights 
    Law Clinic, et al., complaint (lawsuit) filed Feb. 8, 1996 to challenge 
    the constitutionality of the section of the '96 Telecom Reform Act that 
    prohibits online dissemination of information relating to abortion.
<DT><a href="crlp_abortion_lawsuit_020896.alert"><B>crlp_abortion_lawsuit_020896.alert</B></a>
<DD>Press release discussing the case, and
    announcing that the Justice Dept. admits the statute is 
    unconstitutional, and has agreed not to attempt to enforce the new law 
    while the case is at trial.
</DL>

